risk: Due to the high mass and energy of this event, a substantial number of fragments have been generated. Work is ongoing to assess the risk to UK licensed satellites however it’s likely that those at lower altitudes such as newly launched OneWeb satellites, Davinci and the Diamond series of CubeSats will have a significant increase in the number of potential collisions due to tracked and untracked debris. Both the International Space Station and the Tiangong Space Station orbit within the affected region and so we would expect to see a significant increase in risk over the short-medium term because of this event.
